      <div class="view-header">
      <div class="sectionheader"><h3>Recent Posts</h3></div>
    </div>
      
      <div class="view-content">
          <div class="views-row"><div class="views-field views-field-field-blog-category"><div class="field-content field-name-field-blog-category"><a href="/blog-categories/poetry" hreflang="en">Poetry</a>
</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-thumbnail"><div class="field-content imageleft">  <a href="/blog/poetry/days-winter-ken-hada" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/blog_thumbnail/public/Cedar-Anchor3.jpg?itok=fjFz6M5o" width="100" height="75" alt="A photograph of a cedar tree blanketed in snow" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-blog-thumbnail" />

</a>

</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><h4 class="field-content"><a href="https://www.worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/poetry/days-winter-ken-hada">In Days of Winter</a>
</h4></div><div><div class="blog-summary">

Marc/Stock.adobe.com

. . . I sleep early, risebefore daylight, waitwith patient stuporthe coming gray light. . . I move slowly,surreptitiously —…
</div></div><span class="views-field views-field-field-date"><span class="field-content date-display-single">February 19, 2025
